#compdef srchx
# =============================================================================
# srchx — alash3al/srchx's STANDALONE LIGHTWEIGHT
#   Go FULL-TEXT SEARCH ENGINE built directly on
#   `blevesearch/bleve` (the canonical pure-Go
#   Lucene-inspired full-text search library).
#   Exposes a JSON-over-HTTP RESTful API at
#   `:2050` with ELASTICSEARCH-SHAPED endpoints
#   (`POST /{index}/{type}/_doc/{id}` to
#   index, `POST /{index}/{type}/_search` to
#   query, etc.).  Dynamic index creation — no
#   pre-flight mapping required, just POST a
#   JSON doc and the index materialises.  Go=105
#   leader bump continuing Axis 50 (Full-Text
#   Search Engine) at the Go pole, opened by
#   R789 `_toshi` (Rust=105, tantivy ^0.19) —
#   the half-century axis landmark.
#
# AXIS 50 — FULL-TEXT SEARCH ENGINE — GO POLE
# ============================================
# `blevesearch/bleve` (10.7k+ stars on GitHub,
# Apache-2.0) is the canonical pure-Go Lucene-
# style full-text search library.  Inverted-
# indexed by default, supports phrase / fuzzy /
# wildcard / regex / range / numeric / date /
# geo queries, faceted search, BM25 + TF-IDF
# scoring, segment-based incremental indexing,
# and pluggable storage engines.  Distinguishes
# from other Go search libraries:
#   - blugelabs/bluge: a fork of bleve's "v2"
#     architecture with a more functional API
#     surface.  Used internally by Grafana Loki
#   - sajari/fuzzy / antzucaro/matchr: fuzzy-
#     string libs, not full-text indexes
#   - lindb / vela-search: log-search-specific,
#     not general-purpose
#
# Other Axis 50 implementations across the
# corpus:
#   * Rust       (R789): tantivy ^0.19
#                — bundled in `toshi` (HTTP
#                  daemon, Elasticsearch-shaped
#                  API)
#   * Go         (R790, THIS ROUND):
#                blevesearch/bleve v0.7.0 —
#                bundled in `srchx` (HTTP
#                daemon, Elasticsearch-shaped
#                API)
#   * TS-Node    (R791 will close): elasticlunr
#                / lunr / orama — JS-native
#                search indexes (Node or
#                browser)
#
# PLUGGABLE STORAGE ENGINES (`-engine <NAME>`):
# Bleve supports multiple key/value backends
# under its segment store.  srchx surfaces this
# choice via a single flag:
#   - boltdb   — etcd-io/bbolt, default for
#                srchx.  Pure-Go single-file
#                B+ tree.  No external
#                dependencies, slow writes
#                under contention
#   - leveldb  — syndtr/goleveldb, pure-Go
#                LSM-tree.  Faster writes than
#                BoltDB; tunable compaction
#   - badger   — dgraph-io/badger, pure-Go
#                LSM-tree optimised for SSDs.
#                Concurrent writes; better
#                throughput than goleveldb
#   - scorch   — bleve's native segment-based
#                storage (not a key/value
#                wrapper).  Best for full-text
#                workloads.  Recommended by
#                upstream bleve for new
#                deployments
#
# Distinguishing srchx from sibling corpus
# tools:
#   - srchx vs toshi (R789, Rust):
#       Same architectural shape (HTTP daemon
#       on top of an inverted-index library)
#       but srchx is Go + bleve while toshi is
#       Rust + tantivy.  srchx uses
#       Elasticsearch-style URL pattern
#       `/{index}/{type}/_doc/{id}`; toshi
#       uses `/{index}/_create` + `_search`
#       endpoints (closer to ES newer typeless
#       API).  srchx supports `_aggregate` for
#       term/numeric/date faceting; toshi
#       relies on tantivy's facet field type
#   - srchx vs gitea / grafana / alist /
#     LocalAI (bleve-using corpus binaries
#     already covered): each of those uses
#     bleve as an INTERNAL search index for
#     their domain (issue search, dashboards,
#     file metadata, AI prompts).  srchx is a
#     STANDALONE search daemon — its only
#     purpose is to serve bleve over HTTP
#   - srchx vs git-bug (also direct bleve
#     dep): git-bug embeds bleve to search
#     git-stored bug comments.  Different
#     domain entirely; srchx is general-
#     purpose
#
# CLI ARGUMENT PARSER — Go stdlib `flag`
# package.  All flags use SINGLE DASH long
# form (`-listen`, not `--listen`).  Go's
# `flag` parser also accepts the GNU-style
# `--listen` for compatibility (treated as
# the same flag).  No subcommands; the
# binary is a single long-running daemon
# process.
#
# CLI FLAGS (verbatim from `vars.go`):
#   * `-listen <ADDR>`         REST server bind
#                              address.  Default
#                              `:2050`
#   * `-engine <NAME>`         bleve storage
#                              backend.  Default
#                              `boltdb`.  See
#                              "PLUGGABLE
#                              STORAGE ENGINES"
#                              above for the
#                              full list
#   * `-storage <PATH>`        on-disk index
#                              directory.
#                              Default `<binary
#                              location>/data`
#   * `-workers <N>`           GOMAXPROCS for
#                              the runtime.
#                              Default
#                              `runtime.NumCPU()`
#   * `-testdata <N>`          generate N fake
#                              documents in a
#                              `test/fake`
#                              collection at
#                              startup (uses
#                              icrowley/fake to
#                              synth full_name +
#                              country + brand +
#                              email + ip +
#                              industry + age +
#                              salary + power +
#                              family fields).
#                              Default `0`
#                              (no test data)
#
# CRITICAL DIRECT DEPENDENCIES (from go.mod):
#   - github.com/blevesearch/bleve v0.7.0
#                              — Lucene-style
#                                full-text
#                                search library
#                                [AXIS 50 LIBRARY]
#   - github.com/alash3al/libsrchx
#                              — maintainer's
#                                wrapper around
#                                bleve (Store
#                                + Index
#                                abstractions
#                                with pluggable
#                                engines)
#   - github.com/labstack/echo v3.3
#                              — HTTP server
#                                framework
#                                (replaces
#                                net/http)
#   - github.com/labstack/gommon
#                              — common echo
#                                utilities
#   - github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go v3.2
#                              — JWT
#                                (currently
#                                indirect)
#   - github.com/icrowley/fake — fake-data
#                                generator
#                                (powers the
#                                `-testdata`
#                                flag)
#
# Go 1.x (no explicit MSRV in go.mod — the
# `module` block lacks a `go` directive,
# implying pre-Go-1.12).  Builds with any
# modern Go.  Single-file deployment;
# release binaries published per-platform on
# GitHub Releases.
#
# REST API CHEAT SHEET (verbatim from
# main.go routing):
#   * POST   /:index/:type/_doc/:id
#               index a single document
#               (path-id, body is JSON doc)
#   * POST   /:index/:type/_docs
#               batch-index multiple
#               documents (body is JSON
#               array)
#   * GET    /:index/:type/_doc/:id
#               retrieve a document by id
#   * DELETE /:index/:type/_doc/:id
#               delete a document by id
#   * POST   /:index/:type/_search
#               search the index (body is a
#               bleve Query JSON +
#               from/size/sort)
#   * POST   /:index/:type/_aggregate/:field/:func
#               aggregate over a field with
#               function `:func`
#               (terms/numeric/date)
#   * GET    /
#               liveness probe + info banner
#
# UPSTREAM:
#   * Source             : https://github.com/alash3al/srchx
#   * bleve              : https://github.com/blevesearch/bleve
#   * bleve docs         : http://blevesearch.com
#   * Bleve QueryString  : http://blevesearch.com/docs/Query-String-Query/
#   * Postman API docs   : https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/2408647/RznBLzUY
#   * License            : unclear (no LICENSE file in repo)
#   * Maintainer         : alash3al
#
# INSTALL:
#   # From source
#   go install github.com/alash3al/srchx@latest
#
#   # Pre-built binaries
#   # https://github.com/alash3al/srchx/releases
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
#
#   # Run with defaults (listen :2050, boltdb
#   # engine, data/ next to binary, all CPUs)
#   srchx
#
#   # Bind a different address
#   srchx -listen 0.0.0.0:8080
#   srchx --listen 127.0.0.1:9200
#
#   # Use the scorch storage engine
#   # (recommended for new full-text deployments)
#   srchx -engine scorch
#
#   # Use badger storage on SSD-backed disk
#   srchx -engine badger \
#         -storage /mnt/ssd/srchx-data
#
#   # Cap CPU usage at 4 workers (useful for
#   # shared hosts)
#   srchx -workers 4
#
#   # Seed with 10,000 fake records for
#   # benchmarking
#   srchx -testdata 10000
#
#   # Help (Go stdlib `flag` default behaviour)
#   srchx -h
#   srchx --help
#
# CLIENT-SIDE HTTP EXAMPLES (from upstream
# README):
#
#   # Index a tweet
#   curl -X POST 'http://localhost:2050/twitter/tweets/_doc/new' \
#       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#       -d '{
#         "user": "u5",
#         "content": "this is my tweet",
#         "views": 5
#       }'
#
#   # Retrieve by id
#   curl http://localhost:2050/twitter/tweets/_doc/<uuid>
#
#   # Query-string search
#   curl -X POST http://localhost:2050/twitter/tweets/_search \
#       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#       -d '{
#         "query": "tweet",
#         "size": 10,
#         "from": 0,
#         "sort": ["-views"]
#       }'
#
#   # Aggregate: top countries
#   curl -X POST http://localhost:2050/test/fake/_aggregate/country/terms \
#       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#       -d '{"query": "*"}'
#
# OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/alash3al/srchx/blob/master/vars.go):
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

local -a _srchx_engines
_srchx_engines=(
    'boltdb:etcd-io/bbolt single-file B+ tree (default; no concurrent writes)'
    'leveldb:syndtr/goleveldb pure-Go LSM-tree'
    'badger:dgraph-io/badger SSD-optimised pure-Go LSM-tree (concurrent writes)'
    'scorch:bleve native segment-based store (recommended for full-text)'
)

_arguments -C \
    '(- *)'{-h,-help,--help}'[show usage help]' \
    '-listen=[REST server bind address (default :2050)]:host:port: ' \
    '-engine=[bleve storage backend]:engine:->engine' \
    '-storage=[on-disk index directory (default <bindir>/data)]:dir:_files -/' \
    '-workers=[GOMAXPROCS for the runtime (default runtime.NumCPU())]:n: ' \
    '-testdata=[generate N fake records in a test/fake collection at startup (default 0)]:n: ' \
    && ret=0

case $state in
    engine)
        _describe -t engines 'bleve storage engine' _srchx_engines && ret=0 ;;
esac

return ret
